# IP Development Memory

When working on an IP, do not rely on the chat transcript as the only memory.
The durable memory lives inside the IP folder.

## Start of IP work

Run this once when an IP becomes the work target:

```bash
python3 scripts/ip_dev_memory.py init <ip>
```

This creates or checks:

- `<ip>/wiki/index.md`
- `<ip>/wiki/log.md`
- `<ip>/wiki/llm_memory.md`
- `<ip>/wiki/git.md`
- `<ip>/.git/`

If `<ip>/.git/` does not exist, initialize it. Use local git config inside the
IP folder; do not rely on global git identity.

## During development

At each meaningful stage boundary, write a short memory entry:

```bash
python3 scripts/ip_dev_memory.py log <ip> \
  --stage sim \
  --title "scoreboard mismatch reproduced" \
  --body "Observed pwm_out high for 1 extra cycle when DUTY changes." \
  --evidence <ip>/sim/scoreboard_events.jsonl
```

Then snapshot the IP-local repository after evidence or behavior changes:

```bash
python3 scripts/ip_dev_memory.py snapshot <ip> --message "sim: reproduce duty update mismatch"
```

## Before claiming completion

Run:

```bash
python3 scripts/ip_dev_memory.py check <ip> --require-git
```

Completion should mention the wiki/git evidence alongside ROCEV evidence.
